{"id":144624753,"lang":"java","time":"3 years, 9 months","timestamp":1520812952,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"65 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/144624753/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"N/A","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode(int x) { val = x; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        \n            int sum;\n            int carry=0;\n         ListNode res = null; \n         ListNode prev = null;\n         ListNode temp = null;\n       \n        while(l1!=null || l2!=null)\n        {\n            sum=carry + (l1 != null ? l1.val : 0) + (l2 != null ? l2.val : 0);\n            carry = (sum >= 10) ? 1 : 0;\n            sum = sum % 10;\n            temp = new ListNode(sum);\n\n            if (res == null) {\n                res = temp;\n            } \n            else{\n                prev.next = temp;\n            }\n          prev = temp;\n            if (l1 != null) {\n                l1 = l1.next;\n            }\n            if (l2 != null) {\n                l2 = l2.next;\n            }\n        }   if (carry > 0) {\n            temp.next = new ListNode(carry);\n        }\n \n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers"}
